On Sat, 22 Nov 2003, Sage Green wrote:

> Hints solicited:
>
> How do I insure my head gaskets do not slip and become 'pinched' when I put
> my heads on??
>
> also, same question for the exhaust gaskets on the '72.

Two questions, one answer:  Grease.  A dab of grease will stick the
gaskets to the heads during installation.  On the exhaust gaskets it may
also be necessary to peen the edge of the hole a bit.

